pr_body:
* Fixes an exception that could happen when adding authors
  in a JATS conversion.

@fschwenn

…proto installation instructions.

fixes #624 

@oxtopus please review

__NOTE__: This PR updates the `__version__` in cloudaux/__about__.py

* The previous PR mistakenly used Python's __HTTPException__ instead of __openstack.exceptions.HttpException__.  This PR properly imports and uses the latter.

@mikegrima

Works pretty well I think.

I ran into https://github.com/github/git-lfs/issues/913 and https://github.com/github/git-lfs/issues/914 while implementing, but it should mostly work.

@JannKleen it took me a while but I finally got around to this :)

@bersace 

Take a look at project restructuring I suggest. In such a way we can have a modularity with core functionality in `pylogctx` package and specialized functionality in `ext` package.

P.S.: And there is a question - who will own this package on pypi :)

I removed the version pinning on tornado.  Recent bokeh releases should no longer need this. 

I removed the jupyter_dashboards reference, although I'm ignorant of its original purpose

@martindurant at some point it would be nice to refresh your docker image for use with dask-kubernetes
